%S A395777 1,2,3,4,4,6,6,8,9,8,10,12,14,12,12,16,18,18,20,16,18,20,24,24,20,28,
%T A395777 27,24,28,24,30,32,30,36,24,36,38,40,42,32,42,36,44,40,36,48,48,48,42,
%U A395777 40,54,56,52,54,40,48,60,56,58,48,62,60,54,64,56,60,68,72,72,48
%N A395777 The twisted Euler phi-function for the Dirichlet character kronecker(-24,.) mod 24.
%C A395777 We have h(-24*n^2), the class number of the order of Z[sqrt(-6)] with discriminant -24*n^2, is equal to 2*a(n).
%C A395777 In general, let d < 0 be a fundamental discriminant and n be a positive integer such that d*n^2 < -4, then h(d*n^2) = L(0,kronecker(d,.)) * n * Product_{p|n, p prime} (1 - kronecker(d,p)/p). This is a combination of Theorem 7.24 in "Primes of the form x^2+ny^2" by Cox and the Dirichlet class number formula. Here L(0,kronecker(-24,.)) = 2.
%D A395777 D. A. Cox, Primes of the form x^2+ny^2, Wiley, New York, 1989, p. 146.
%H A395777 Jianing Song, <a href="/A395777/b395777.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000</a>
%F A395777 Multiplicative with a(2^e) = 2^e, a(3^e) = 3^e, a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p-1) if p == 1, 5, 7, 11 (mod 24) and a(p^e) = p^(e-1)*(p+1) if p == 13, 17, 19, 23 (mod 24).
%e A395777 Given L(0,kronecker(-24,.)) = 2, we have: h(-24*1^2) = 2*a(1) = 2, h(-24*2^2) = 2*a(2) = 4, h(-24*3^2) = 2*a(3) = 6, h(-24*4^2) = 2*a(4) = 8, ...
%o A395777 (PARI) a(n,{d=-24}) = my(f=factor(n)[,1]~, w=#f); n * prod(i=1, w, 1 - kronecker(d,f[i])/f[i])
%Y A395777 A109017 is the corresponding Dirichlet character.
%Y A395777 Cf. for fundamental discriminants -3..-24: A227128, A395768, A395771, A395769, A395772, A395773, A395774, A395775, A395776, this sequence.
%K A395777 nonn,easy,mult,new
%O A395777 1,2
%A A395777 _Jianing Song_, May 05 2026
